timeAtRisks.description: TAR 1: Primary on-treatment analysis with 3-day gap (DOACs) or 7-day gap (warfarin) plus 5 days appended
TAR 2: On-treatment sensitivity analysis with a 30-day gap and no days appended
TAR 1: 30 days to 15 years after IUD placement
TAR 2: 1 year to 15 years after IUD placement
TAR 1: intention-to-treat (ITT), which followed patients until the end of data availability
TAR 3: during treatment, which followed people from 1 day after the index date until the completion of the treatment
TAR 4: during treatment with a 1-year lag
